// AUTO-GENERATED ASSET — do not edit by hand.
//
// Packaged-app startup splash animation, embedded as a base64 `data:` URL so it
// is compiled straight into the desktop main bundle. We intentionally inline it
// instead of shipping a loose file: the desktop runtime resolves no reliable
// on-disk asset path inside the packaged `.app` (the existing icon lookup in
// runtime.ts already falls back to null there), so a filesystem asset would not
// render in production. Inlining guarantees identical behaviour in dev and in
// packaged builds with zero electron-builder file-inclusion wiring.
//
// Provenance: first clean loop (0 -> 1.7s) of the brand intro animation, the
// alpha channel flattened onto a solid white background and re-encoded to VP9.
// The clip ends on the fully-settled "Open design" logo, which is also the
// frame the <video> freezes on (loop disabled) while the web runtime finishes
// booting. ~29KB base64.
//
// To regenerate from a source webm SRC:
//   ffmpeg -c:v libvpx-vp9 -i SRC -filter_complex \
//     "[0:v]trim=start=0:end=1.7,setpts=PTS-STARTPTS,format=yuva420p[v];\
//      color=white:s=848x500:d=1.7[bg];[bg][v]overlay=shortest=1,format=yuv420p[out]" \
//     -map "[out]" -c:v libvpx-vp9 -crf 36 -b:v 0 -an splash.webm
//   then base64-encode splash.webm into SPLASH_VIDEO_DATA_URL below.

export const SPLASH_VIDEO_DATA_URL = "data:video/webm;base64,";
